[SN]TITLE[SN]
Family tribute to man killed after being hit by car on A91 near Collessie

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The family of a Fife man who died after being hit by a car on the A91 has paid tribute to the "loving husband and father" saying he would be "sadly missed".

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Alistair Forbes, 47, was knocked down at the junction with the B937, near Collessie, at about 21:05 on Saturday.
His family said: "Alistair was a loving husband and father who will be sadly missed by all who knew him."
Police Scotland have appealed for witnesses.
